The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as Variational Autoencoder and Graph Convolutional Networks for the analysis of functional brain networks. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of graph theory and computer vision techniques, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
